40
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,880
I'm from the satellite near that star.

41
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,720
You're an alien.

42
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,600
Are you really an alien?

43
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:51,440
You don't believe it?

44
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,440
Definitely no.

45
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,160
If you said you had powers,
I'd believe you,

46
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,360
but you're saying you're M2,

47
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,520
that just isn't scientific.

48
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,600
Eight million light years away.

49
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,320
How's that even possible?

50
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,520
That's beautiful.

51
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,000
Alright, I believe you.

52
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,240
If you really came from another planet,

53
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,440
then you're welcome here.

54
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,800
Welcome to our home, Earth.

55
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,000
But our clan leader said,

56
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,240
